<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-10-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-10-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="825" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d825">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/782</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-06">October 6, 1931</date>.<lb/>[Received October
                                14.]</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 2297</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to refer to the
                            Department’s instruction No. 852, July 14, 1931,<note n="5" xml:id="d825fn5">Not printed.</note> relating to the proposed new
                            treaty on extraterritorial rights of the United States in China, and to
                            state that the memorandum forwarded therewith<note n="6" xml:id="d825fn6">For pertinent portions of memorandum, see telegram
                                No. 228, July 13, to the Minister in China, <ref target="#pg_890">p.
                                    890</ref>.</note> was duly delivered to the Foreign Office.
                            There is attached hereto a copy of a memorandum in reply prepared by the
                            Foreign Office, dated October 5, 1931,<note n="5" xml:id="d825fn7">Not
                                printed.</note> which was handed to a member of the Embassy staff
                            without comment.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                        <closer>(For the Ambassador)<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Ray
                                    Atherton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>